<P>
HILLBILLY BIAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re "Bias Blights Life Outside Appalachia," March 29: 
</P>
<P>
 What's all the fuss about "hillbilly" bias? I am proud to be a full-fledged 
West Virginia hillbilly whose dad was raised up "Catfish Holler," whose 
95-year-old grandmother just got running water, and whose grandfather was once 
a coal miner. 
</P>
<P>
 Did I experience discrimination when I left the Appalachians to work a summer 
job in Columbus, Ohio, or when I graduated from college and journeyed to Los 
Angeles? No. But I also came from a family that valued a good education and 
high achievement. 
</P>
<P>
 SUSAN CARRIER 
</P>
<P>
 San Gabriel 
