<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rob Chavez was hired from Maryland Eastern Shore to coach at the University of 
Portland. Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Third-seeded Richey Reneberg defeated 1993 NCAA champion Chris Woodruff, 6-1, 
6-2, in the first round of the $288,750 Eddleman U.S. Clay Court Championships 
at Birmingham, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Tarango, ranked 103rd, upset sixth-seeded and 43rd-ranked Jonathan Stark, 
6-2, 6-3, in the first round of the Salem Tennis Open in Hong Kong. Names in 
the News 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Giannini was hired as athletic director at Northeast Louisiana 
University. 
