<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dealer Inventory Falls in March: U.S. inventories of domestically made 
vehicles from General Motors Corp., Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. declined 
to a 58-day supply in late March from 62 days as of Feb. 28, according to 
Ward's Automotive Reports. The Big Three auto makers are straining to get 
enough vehicles on dealer lots to meet increased demand, especially in the 
light-truck category. 
</P>
