SID WEISS; PLAYED BASS FOR PROMINENT BIG BANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sid Weiss, 79, bassist with most of the prominent big bands of the 1930s and 
'40s and a fixture in Los Angeles recording studios.Weiss, a native of 
Schenectady, N.Y., studied the bass there and later with the principal bassist 
of the Washington, D.C., Symphony. He joined Louie Prima's band in the early 
1930s and during the next 20 years toured and recorded with Artie Shaw, Benny 
Goodman, Jerry Wald, Charlie Barnett and others. Most recently he had served as 
a deputy state labor commissioner, a field he became involved in through the 
American Federation of Musicians. In Colton on March 29 of the complications of 
heart surgery. 
