<P>
 Tennis / Singles 
</P>
<P>
 O'Neill started slowly in his set against Canyon's No. 1 player Paul Espinoza 
Thursday. O'Neill trailed love-40 before Espinoza broke him in the first 
game.But he stayed in the set, broke Espinoza at 5-6 and went on to win the 
tiebreaker, 8-6. It was O'Neill's only tough set of the day; he won the other 
two, 6-3, 6-1, helping the Panthers to a 10 2/3-10 1/3 victory over Canyon, 
then ranked ninth in the county. Led by O'Neill, who is 27-0 this season, 
Orange is challenging the Century League's traditional tennis powers, Canyon, 
Villa Park and Foothill. Other notables: 
