<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carrie Garritson 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Track / Distance 
</P>
<P>
 Garritson didn't take it easy during the days leading up to the Arcadia 
Invitational.She ran the 880, mile, two-mile and the mile relay in two dual 
meets, winning each of the individual races and helping the Coyotes in a loss 
to Sonora and a victory over Sunny Hills. Then Saturday, she won the 3,200 
meters in 10 minutes 39.33 seconds, the best high school time in the nation 
this season. It's not Garritson's best, however; she set the Orange County 
record of 10:28.2 during her sophomore year, running for Sunny Hills. Other 
notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Kristi Bolle, El Modena, batted .538 with three homers and 11 RBIs and 
struck out eight in six innings to pick up a victory. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lisa Hess, Canyon, won the 100 butterfly in a county-best 1:00.40 and the 
200 free (1:59.9) in a victory over Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 * Linda Rodriguez, La Quinta, drove in a run in a 1-0 victory over Arroyo 
Grande in the title game of the San Luis Obispo tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nicola Walsh, Rosary, gave up three runs in 35 innings, struck out 35 in 
five victories, including a no-hitter, and batted .571 with seven stolen bases. 
</P>
