<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; ESPERANZA EASILY BEATS BREA IN GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza had four players shoot under par as the Aztecs beat Brea-Olinda, 
171-207, in a nonleague golf match Monday at Imperial Golf Course in Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Berry shot a four-under 32 for Esperanza. Scott Lucidi, Jason Henderson 
and Bill Kelly each shot 34 for Esperanza (11-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague golf: 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 200, Western 212 -- Ben Garner of El Toro and Tiger Woods of Western, 
two of the best prep golfers in Southern California, tied at one-over 36 at 
Cypress Golf Club. Each had two birdies. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 216, Mater Dei 226 -- Scott Jordan was the medalist for Mater Dei 
(4-4, 0-3), shooting a three-over 39 at Tijeras Creek. San Clemente remains 
undefeated in league at 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunset League girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster 92, Santa Ana 34 -- Shana Munyer won the 800, the 1,600 and the 
3,200, and teammate Johanna Haggerty also won the high jump with a leap of 5 
feet 3, which tied the school record for Westminster (1-3, 1-3). She also won 
the long jump and the triple jump. 
</P>
<P>
 In Pacific Coast League girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 97, Costa Mesa 26 -- Karine Inoye of Laguna Hills (2-0) won both 
hurdle events finishing the 100 in 16.3 and the 300 in 52.0. 
</P>
<P>
 In Pacific Coast League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 90, Costa Mesa 42 -- Brandon McGraw won the 100 (11.2) and 200 
(23.2) for Laguna Hills (2-0). Teammate Jesse McDonald threw his personal best 
in the discus (160-4), finishing first, and also won the shotput (43-5 3/4). 
Shaheed Quaasim ran the 110 hurdles in 15.1, but was disqualified at the end of 
the meet for participating in five events. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 11, Aliso Niguel 10 -- Brent Hankey swept at No. 1 singles, 6-2, 
6-0, 6-2, and Paul Kerwin won, 6-0, 6-0, 6-0, at No. 2 for host Mater Dei 
(3-4). Miles Simon and Austin Harris won at No. 1 doubles, 6-2, 6-0, 6-0, also 
for the Monarchs. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 17, Laguna Beach 4 -- In singles, Geoff Abrams swept his sets 
without losing a game, 6-0, 6-0, 6-0, in the Sailors' victory. Jeff Thomsen 
also swept his sets, 6-4, 6-0, 6-0, and Mark Utman won, 6-3, 6-3, 6-2. In 
doubles, Peter Koss and Chris Ketcham won, 6-4, 6-2, 6-1, for Newport Harbor 
(6-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 17 2/3, Santiago 3 1/3 -- In singles, Eliseo Amezcua swept his 
sets, 6-4, 7-6, 6-1, for Saddleback (5-6). In doubles, Mario Sanchez and Minh 
Nguy won, 6-1, 6-2, 6-2, and Lam Nguyen and Dung Truong won, 6-1, 6-0, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 11 1/3, Cerritos 9 2/3 -- Chris Tobolski and Nick Lovric swept at 
Nos. 1 and 2 singles for Valencia (5-7). 
</P>
