<TEXT>
<P>
 Kent Sullivan, a former Cal Lutheran punter, signed with the San Diego 
Chargers, the NFL team announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan is a beneficiary of the NFL's new salary cap. He replaces John Kidd, 
an unrestricted free agent who made $500,000 last season. Terms of Sullivan's 
contract were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan, who will turn 30 May 15, was with the Chargers three times last year 
when Kidd was hurt, and punted in two games. STEVEN HERBERT 
