DIGEST: TRACK AND FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kay Nekota of Agoura High, the runner-up in the state Division I cross-country 
championships in 1991 and 1993, has committed to UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Nekota took recruiting trips to Cornell, Irvine, Arizona and Penn State before 
choosing the Big West Conference school. She will join former Agoura teammates 
Tiffany York and Tiffany Burt. 
</P>
<P>
 Nekota, a straight-A student, has personal bests of 5 minutes 0.98 seconds in 
the 1,600 meters and 10:52.68 in the 3,200. She placed third in the 1,600 and 
fourth in the 3,200 in last year's Southern Section Division I track 
championships. JOHN ORTEGA 
