<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; ANTI-SEMITIC FLYERS FOUND AT 2 SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 150 anti-Semitic flyers were found stuffed inside student lockers at 
two Mission Viejo schools Monday, less than three months after similar 
incidents in San Juan Capistrano and Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Students at Los Alisos Intermediate School and Mission Viejo High School found 
the flyers Monday morning after returning from a weeklong spring break, said 
Elaine Carter, a spokeswoman for the Saddleback Valley Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alisos, which has students from Mission Viejo, Lake Forest and Laguna 
Hills, was the hardest hit with 150 of the flyers found on campus, Carter said. 
A much smaller number of the same flyers were found at the high school, Carter 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Administrators from both schools responded immediately by discussing the 
incidents with students on a public intercom, and a letter will be sent home to 
all parents indicating that the school is "not responsible for this deplorable 
type of literature," Carter said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to reassure parents that we are on top of this," Carter said. "The 
community needs to know we will act in a timely fashion. We will not tolerate 
this type of thing on our campuses." 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies, representatives of the Orange County Human Relations 
Commission and the Anti-Defamation League, and three rabbis from local temples 
were notified of the incidents, Carter said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jonathan Bernstein, regional director of the Anti-Defamation League, said the 
group's legal affairs division is looking into this "vile stuff." He added that 
the group is looking into some "counter programming" and will send a letter to 
all county principals alerting them to the flyer incidents. 
</P>
<P>
 In January, racist flyers aimed at Latinos were distributed in lockers at 
Marco Forster Middle School and Laguna Beach High School.LEN HALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
