<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; PLAN TO DEVELOP PARK AT SITE TO BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Plans to develop a 48-acre park near City Hall will be discussed during a 
joint meeting of the City Council and Community Services Commission tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents who live in the nearby Westpark village have long suggested that 
vacant land on Harvard Avenue be converted into a recreation area. 
</P>
<P>
 A plan calling for the development of athletics fields, green spaces and 
walkways will be unveiled at tonight's meeting. The plan was drawn up after 
architects held a community meeting to hear residents' ideas. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the plan, the park would be connected by walk paths to the Civic Center 
and nearby child-care center. 
</P>
