 Mercado stopped to help her, police said, and she got into his car. The 
attacker, whom police decline to identify, then allegedly followed them in a 
pickup truck. When Mercado stopped and got out of his car to confront him, the 
man ran him over, police said, and then fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Family members said Mercado's body will be flown to Mexico, where he will be 
buried in his hometown of Sombrerete. He leaves two daughters, Trininad, 16, 
and Consuelo, 8. He was not married at the time he was killed. 
</P>
<P>
 His sister-in-law described him as being particularly close to his brothers. 
"He loves baseball," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He and his brothers played every Sunday. The team won't be complete anymore." 
CHAU LAM 
</P>
