<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARLSON BROTHERS COMMIT TO SCC TO PLAY BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kevin Carlson and his younger brother, Brian, made oral commitments to play 
basketball at Southern California College, Vanguard Coach Bill Reynolds said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin, a 6-foot-5 forward, was a two-time All-Orange Empire Conference 
selection for Fullerton College.He averaged 14 points as a sophomore and 17 
points as a freshman, finishing with 1,044 points, ninth best in Fullerton 
history. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian, who will finish his freshman year at Cal State Fullerton this spring, 
was a walk-on but did not play. He averaged 19 points and 10 rebounds as a 
senior at Katella High in 1992-93. 
</P>
<P>
 "I feel both can come in and play immediately," Reynolds said. 
</P>
<P>
 Reynolds said the Carlsons also plan to continue their track and field careers 
as high jumpers at SCC. 
</P>
<P>
 The Carlsons join former Orange County high school standouts Chris Kostoff of 
Capistrano Valley and Chauncey Woolridge of Santa Ana, who also made oral 
commitments to SCC. 
</P>
