<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regulator Seeks Undercover Mutual Fund Checks: Comptroller of the Currency 
Eugene Ludwig proposed having the federal government use "testers" to check 
whether banks, brokerages and mutual fund firms are adequately warning 
customers of the risks of mutual funds. He called on the heads of the other 
three bank and thrift agencies and the head of the Securities and Exchange 
Commission to form a task force to develop uniform procedures for looking into 
sales practices by all institutions that peddle funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
