VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: ADVANCED PHOTONIX IN PACT TO DEVELOP SCANNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Advanced Photonix, a Camarillo producer of photodetector devices, has signed 
an agreement with the U.S. Department of Energy's Brookhaven National 
Laboratory to jointly develop a new medical scanner. 
</P>
<P>
 The two partners expect to spend a total of $250,000 this year to fund the 
project. Advanced Photonix said the scanner, if successfully marketed, could 
increase its annual revenues by $5 million. 
</P>
<P>
