<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: BIOPOOL GETS FDA'S OK TO MARKET NEW LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biopool International Inc., a Ventura producer of medical test kits, has 
received federal Food and Drug Administration approval to market a new lilene 
of controls used in drug abuse testing. 
</P>
<P>
 The new line includes seven different controls for a total of 10 drugs 
commonly used in random testing, pre-employment screening and the testing of 
persons in parole and probation programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael D. Bick, Biopool's chairman and chief executive, said such controls, 
which verify a test's accuracy, represent a $30-million U.S. market and a 
$60-million worldwide market. 
</P>
<P>
 Biopool, founded in 1987, now produces about 40 tests and controls, mostly for 
diagnosing bleeding and vascular disorders. 
</P>
