<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: HAMBURGER HAMLET BEING SUED BY SHAREHOLDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hamburger Hamlet Restaurants Inc. in Sherman Oaks said that the company and 
some of its present and former executives and directors have been sued by a 
shareholder who alleges the defendants violated certain securities laws by 
concealing adverse information about the company and making false and 
misleading statements. 
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit, filed on March 29 in U. S. District Court in Los Angeles by Mark 
Pfeifer, seeks class action status.It asks for an unspecified amount of 
compensatory and punitive damages, attorneys fees and "equitable relief to 
preserve assets," Hamburger Hamlet said. 
</P>
<P>
 The company and the other defendants deny the allegations, Hamburger Hamlet 
said in a statement, and "intend to aggressively oppose the suit." 
</P>
<P>
 Hamburger Hamlet, whose earnings have fallen because of the weak local 
economy, owns and operates 35 restaurants, most in Southern California. 
</P>
