<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOTERS GO TO POLLS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 50 local elections will be held across Los Angeles County today, 
including one that has gained national attention as a possible referendum on 
gun control. 
</P>
<P>
 Longtime state Sen. David A. Roberti (D-Van Nuys) was forced into a recall 
election by a coalition of groups angered by his authorship of legislation that 
banned military-style assault weapons in California. Most of the other contests 
are for city council seats. 
</P>
<P>
 The polls generally are open from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m, although the Los Angeles 
County registrar's office cautions the hours may vary slightly in some cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
