<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wahlco Environmental Systems: The company said Monday that its Santa Ana-based 
subsidiary, Wahlco Inc., will install its pollution control system at a large 
power plant in Webster, Tex.Terms of the contract, awarded by Houston Lighting 
& Power Co., were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Wahlco said it expects to complete installation of the system -- which reduces 
the emission of nitrous oxide, a component of acid rain -- in December, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Wahlco Environmental Systems, based in Irvine, designs and manufactures air 
pollution control systems for electric utilities, cogeneration plants, 
petrochemical refineries and industrial manufacturers. 
</P>
